707771f-a.folder: 2nd Ave. & St. Mark's Pl., Manhattan, NY
707771f-a.text:
135 West Side, 2nd Avenue, showing Ottendorfer Branch of the N.Y. Public Library between St. Marks Place and East 9th Street.
Victor Volnar.
Neg. #990

707772f-a.text:
137 Second Ave., West side, between East 8th (St. Mark's Place), and East 9th Streets. Occupant of premises is the Stuyvesant Polyclinic Hospital, formerly known as the German Dispensary.

November 5th, 1936.

P.L. Sperr.

Second Avenue, west side, north from St. Mark's Place (8th Street), showing the west side above 11th Street.

June 25, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.

723107f-a.folder: St. Marks Place & 2nd Avenue, Manhattan, NY
723107f-a.text:
19-23, 25 and 27 St. Mark's Place, north side, between Third and Second Aves. The 4-story house (Nos. 19-23, only part of which is shown), is to-day (1937) the Polish National Home Building.
About 1915.
Neg. #754

723108f-a.folder: St. Marks Place & 2nd Avenue, Manhattan, NY
723108f-a.text:
(1)
37 St. Marks Place (East 8th Street), at the N.W. corner of Second Ave., showing the lower floors of the 4-story Alice Keteltas mansion being dismantled. On its site now (1937) stands the 5-story Kiss Building.

About 1913.
Gift of Samuel Landsman.

(2)
The same, another view.

About 1913.
Gift of Sammuel Landsman.
